*.egg-info
.DS_Store
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.venv/
.venv-*/
.idsa-venv/
.suplex/
SUPLEX.md
.pytest_cache/
.pytest_tmp/
results/checkpoints/
results/**/checkpoints/
# Legacy nested-under-run-dir activation layout (e.g. results/runs/pc/seed_0000/
# activations/), NOT the top-level results/activations/ store, which is pushed
# on purpose below. Scoped under runs*/ specifically — "**" matches zero path
# segments, so an unscoped "results/**/activations/" would also match (and
# silently re-ignore) the top-level store itself.
results/runs*/**/activations/
results/**/*.pt
results/**/*.pth
results/**/*.ckpt

# Regenerable run artifacts. Stage 0 rebuilds data/; Stage 1-3 rebuild results/.
# results/figures/ is deliberately NOT ignored — curated figures are committed.
# results/runs/ and results/activations/ (the live 10-seed sweep) are pushed on
# purpose (team hand-off) — checkpoints (.pt) inside them still get excluded via
# the results/**/*.pt rule above regardless. Ad hoc one-off dirs outside the live
# tree (results/runs_v5/ etc.) still need routing into results/archive/ (ignored
# below) rather than relying on a blanket runs*/ pattern like before.
data/raw/
data/processed/
results/rsa/
results/idsa/
# Cluster stdout/stderr per array task -- operational debug output, not a
# result, and specific to whoever's cluster account/paths ran the job.
results/slurm_logs/

# results/archive/ holds superseded pre-cluster pilot runs, kept locally for the
# record but not meant to be pushed. Note: results/archive/{bptt_activity_demo,
# bptt_pilot_all,pc_activity,pc_activity_pre_merge_2026-07-21} were already
# tracked (git-mv'd from results/figures/, which is deliberately not ignored)
# before this rule was added — gitignore doesn't untrack already-tracked files,
# so those stay tracked unless explicitly `git rm --cached`.
results/archive/
